        {
          "scid": "sn52.14:1.1",
          "pli": "“Imesañca panāhaṃ, āvuso, catunnaṃ satipaṭṭhānānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘sarāgaṃ cittan’ti pajānāmi … pe … avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ ‘avimuttaṃ cittan’ti pajānāmī”ti. ",
          "en": "“… And it’s because of developing and cultivating these four kinds of mindfulness meditation that I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. I understand mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’ … I understand unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn52.14:1.2",
          "pli": "Catutthaṃ. ",
